      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EMERALD HILLS (7) ticks a few boxes today after getting the got the job done in grand style, shedding her Maiden status over this trip at Newcastle. Similar set-up for this and expected to go on with it now. SERPICO (5) nice return over the shorter trip when he launched late to get off the mark in a 1350m Super Maiden at Wyong. Should have little trouble running a strong mile and watch for him late. LUNA BAY (8) blinkers come off after she found the 1300m too short first-up with a fading eighth over 1300m at Newcastle. Lone victory came second-up and no surprise to see her figure prominently. ANNOINT (1) racing well in weaker grade and working towards a win. Pushed forward from the wide gate with a solid on-pace second over 1400m at Taree. Claim helps again and gets through the conditions.",
